My Experience Building Africa DoorDash for Agriculture
text:
It been over 2 years of setting on this journey of building Doordash for Agriculture, like Doordash logistics have been a key in the success of this, and building in Africa, Nigeria to be precise have come with it uniqueness of challenge. I came across YC materials 2017 and it has help along in the journey, and have since participated in 2 startup school

Three of my experience that I like to share building in the space and learning how it wouldn't work and how it has worked are;

1. Just like many ecommerce that works in Africa build for business, it makes logistics cost worth it and enable avenue to make revenue on logistics.

2. Build on few niche product, this we make a mistake with when starting and till today our platform have multiple product, but really our focus on some select few.

3. Don't there to be all asset light, it is a mistake as inflation favors asset and many of the customer will be sticky all because of the logistics structure and asset all together. (So raise money early and go all in on Asset.

I hope to look back on this and have give away some wisdom and recipe to the success of what we are building, all together it has been a very tough journey and all thanks to grant and supportive founding team to have survive in an industry of low margin and tremendous impact. As Africa have 60% of the world arable land and with the work of digitization we are doing at DayDone holds a huge opportunity to a brighter and more sustainable future for all.
